      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo UQ campaign — 1 200-sample Latin hypercube",
      "description": "A 1 200-sample Latin-hypercube Monte Carlo campaign was executed to propagate uncertainty in blood viscosity (±12 %), rotor tip clearance (±0.05 mm), and inlet velocity profile shape. Output NIH 95th-percentile bound: 2.41 g/100 L. The campaign included first-order Sobol index estimation; viscosity was identified as the dominant contributor (S1 = 0.61). Full Sobol index tables and scatter plots are archived in the UQ dataset. The structured hasSensitivityAnalysis link was inadvertently omitted from the package during assembly; the underlying analysis artefacts exist in the dataset record.",
      "validationMetric": "NIH-P95",
      "metricValue": 2.41,
      "acceptanceBand": 3.0,
      "passed": true
    },
    {
