      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoIs must directly map to the clinical decision QoIs with no surrogate substitution.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the direct regulatory QoI for hemolysis assessment. Validation experiments measured NIH using the same ASTM F1841 protocol required for regulatory submission. No surrogate substitution. Achieved level 4 equals required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation must be performed on the device geometry and operating envelope matching the COU; any surrogate geometry must be justified with similarity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic pump geometry, not the proprietary VAD geometry. A similarity analysis was conducted demonstrating comparable specific speed and hydraulic diameter ratios, but the impeller blade count differs (5 vs. 7). Achieved level 3; required level 5. Largest gap in the assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
